    <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
      <head>Biographical History</head>
      <p>Fulton Lewis III (1936-) is an American journalist, son of broadcast and print 
		journalist Fulton Lewis (1903-1966).   Among other achievements, he covered numerous 
		conflicts in Vietnam, Biafra, Rhodesia, and elsewhere, and served as Director of 
		Research for the House Un-American Activities Committee in the 1950s.  Retired in the 
		1980s, he now (2008) owns and operates a database services company in Florida.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
      <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
      <p>The 
        
        <emph render="bold">Fulton Lewis III Papers</emph> consist of correspondence, 
		subject files, manuscripts, and published material.</p>
      <p>
        <emph render="bold">Correspondence</emph>, both incoming and outgoing, includes fan 
		mail as well as general correspondence.  
        
        <emph render="bold">Subject files</emph> 
		consists of lists, menus, and student papers and reports.  
		
        
        <emph render="bold">Manuscripts</emph> includes columns and commercials as well as 
		manuscripts of radio broadcasts.  
        
        <emph render="bold">Published material</emph> contains 
		newsletters written by Lewis and some weekly newspapers of others.</p>
    </scopecontent>
    <arrangement encodinganalog="351$a">
      <head>Arrangement of the Collection</head>
      <p>Correspondence is arranged alphabetically by correspondent; fan mail is placed 
		separately at the end of the series.  Subject files are arranged alphabetically by 
		topic.  Manuscripts are arranged alphabetically by type of material; within that, 
		radio scripts are arranged chronologically.  Published material is arranged 
		alphabetically by title.</p>
    </arrangement>
